      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, first {{caster-sugar}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Add the {{water}} a tablespoon at a time and bring together. Divide in two (one slightly larger), wrap flat, and chill an hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Filling, assembly",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Mix the {{blueberries}}, second {{caster-sugar}}, {{cornflour}}, zest and juice of the {{lemon}} and {{cinnamon-ground}} in a bowl. Roll the larger pastry disc and line the pie dish. Tip the filling in, doming slightly. Roll the second disc and lay over the top; seal and crimp the edges. Cut five short slashes from the centre out as steam vents.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, two stages",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush with the beaten {{eggs}} and scatter with {{demerara-sugar}}. Set on a tray. Bake at 200°C fan for 20 minutes, then drop to 180°C fan for another 30 to 35 minutes; the pastry should be deep gold and the filling should bubble through the vents. Cool 30 minutes before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
